CompanyDescription.label: Company Description
CompanyDescription.value: The Funds investment objective is to maximize total return through a combination of current income and capital appreciation. Fund invests in a wide range of both fixed income and other debt instruments (Income Securities) selected from a variety of sectors and credit qualities, including, but not limited to, government and agency securities, corporate bonds, loans and loan participations, structured finance investments (including residential and commercial mortgage-related securities, asset-backed securities, collateralized debt obligations and risk-linked securities), mezzanine and preferred securities and convertible securities. The Fund may invest in non-U.S. dollar-denominated Income Securities issued by sovereign entities and corporations, including Income Securities of issuers in emerging market countries. The Fund may invest in Income Securities of any credit quality.
